cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The problem involves covering points in the plane with boxes, which suggests computational geometry (cs.CG) as a likely sub-category. The use of algorithms and running times also suggests data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) as possible sub-categories. The fact that the problem is NP-hard suggests complexity theory (cs.CC) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of optimization techniques and minimizing the area of the largest box suggests game theory (cs.GT) as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
